               <p>On the 17th of March I was going along <placeName id="t17920329-42-crimeloc237">Fleet-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17920329-42-crimeloc237" type="placeName" value="Fleet-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17920329-42-crimeloc237" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17920329-42-off235 t17920329-42-crimeloc237"></join>, the prisoner picked my pocket; I saw him do it; I pursued him, and in the middle of the coach-way he dropped it; I saw him drop it; I picked it up; I gave it to the constable; I never lost sight of the prisoner.</p>
               <p>(The handkerchief produced.)</p>
               <p>The CONSTABLE sworn.</p>
               <p>I received a handkerchief from the prosecutor, which I gave him back again; it was such a handkerchief as this, but I cannot swear to it.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was going along Fleet-street, and hearing the cry of stop thief! I ran, as others did, and the gentleman struck me with his umbrella, and almost knocked me down. I am innocent.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17920329-42-verdict238" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17920329-42-verdict238" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. (Aged 18.)</p>
               <p>
